projects.name: Children playtime planning website
projects.description: This application helps the parents to predict the suitable weather for their childs outdoor playtime. Made using ReactJs, TailwindCss, learnt about how to use react hooks such as useState,useEffect and many more. Learnt about how to fetch APIs and how to implement in the project.

projects.name: SIBYL: Strategic Intelligence For Building Your Legacy
projects.description: Built a complete website for employee career path navigation based on ensemble predictions of RF,DT,SVM and XGBoost models. It provides skill gap, analysis and learning resources and recommendations for upskilling. Deployed via streamlit, upcoming versions to be deployed through Next.js. Adjudged top 3 at Dell Hackathon.

projects.name: Weather website
projects.description: This application helps one to check the weather condition of a place. Made using HTML/CSS, Javascript, learnt about how to fetch APIs and how to implement in the project. Learned how to make changes in your existing document through the document object model.

projects.name: Travel Website
projects.description: Designed a travel website using html/css, javascript, mysql to showcase how dynamic pages works. Learned a lot about CSS frameworks, flex-box, box- model, transitions, how to use bootstrap in your project and also about material UI. Learned how to connect a project to a database and how the data is stored and retrieved.

experiences.description: Led the web development team for Qureka, the college quizzing club, overseeing the creation and maintenance of a dynamic and user-friendly club website.
